               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### On Quality\n\nWhile we prioritize primary sources, critical examination is essential:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 2: Perfection</b><br /><br />Are primary sources perfect?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "An eyewitness account doesn't guarantee complete accuracy. Researchers must gather multiple sources to reconstruct events reliably.\n\nFor example, chronicles disagree about the death date of Musa ibn Fortún, citing either <htdate0> (<htcite0>) or <htdate1> (<htcite1>).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 0,
                     "uuid": "b43eff03-c370-4692-875a-2455e2c99d03",
                     "text": "Juste, Alberto C.",
                     "page": "pp. 9",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "1980",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 0,
                     "uuid": "08577d63-fb3e-4d9b-884d-7e7296beb4a5",
                     "text": "De La Granja, Fernando",
                     "page": "pp. 465",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "1967",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "789",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "802",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### Age and Precision\n\nEarlier texts tend to be less detailed, potentially obscuring meaning and raising questions:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 3: Precision</b><br /><br />Are older texts necessarily more accurate?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "Ancient texts contain words whose meanings have shifted semantically (<htcite0>). Readers often misinterpret metaphorical language as literal (<htcite1>).\n\nThe **Sumerian King List** illustrates this, mixing verifiable rulers with implausible lifespans and localized events described as universal (<htcite2>).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "79ea767b-924d-43e3-9bea-a8195b536dde",
                     "text": "Sabino, Marilei A.",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2011",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "0c59c0de-f385-4bf2-8190-166d53e158b5",
                     "text": "Portuese, Ludovico & Pallavidini, Marta",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2020",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "e8bb14f9-defd-4495-824d-8daf202a7509",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "",
